
            Video
            May: 'The British people want this to be settled'
            PM Theresa May has said a Brexit deal is now "within our grasp".It follows meetings between UK and EU officials in Brussels, where a draft agreement on a future relationship was set out. Speaking outside 10 Downing Street, the PM said: "This is the right deal for the UK. It delivers on the vote of the referendum."
                
                        22 Nov 2018
                    
                
        
